title: Edmonton Statue of Emily Murphy
description: This statue of Emily Murphy in Edmonton was vandalized in 2021. Covered in red paint with the word "racist" across her plaque, sparking debate: should it stay or should it go? Ultimately, with the majority of Calgarian's support, the statue stayed.

title: Women are Persons!
description: This statue of the Famous Five was sculpted by Barbara Paterson, the first sculptor to create a permanent monument on parliment hill dedicated to Canadian Women. This sculpture as unveiled in Calgary's Olympic Plaza in 1999, and a similar one was erected in 2000 in Ottawa.
creator: Barbara Paterson
subject: Famous Five
